gomodel:SYNGO_1788  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig 2a ROCK2 is involved in hippocampal synaptic function\nLiteral \"The sizes of fEPSPs were significantly reduced in ROCK2 knockout mice compared to the wild-type littermates.\"\nFig 3 ROCK2 deletion affects LTP\nLiteral \"As shown in Fig. 3A and B, LTP induced by high frequency stimulation\n(four trains of 100 Hz lasting 1 s each with 20 s intertrain intervals) was significantly reduced in ROCK2 knockout mice compared to the wild-type littermates\"\nFig 5b,c Synapse deficits in ROCK2 knockout mice\nLiteral \"We counted the total number of asymmetric synapses and found that the density was significantly lower in ROCK2\"Interestingly, in addition to a reduction in synapse density, the averaged postsynaptic area or spine area was significantly increased in ROCK2 knockout mice\"\nFig 7c spine deficits in ROCK2 knockout mice\nLiteral \"the spine length was significantly increased in ROCK2 knockout mice.. Experimental description: All the experiments were done in mice\nLiteral \"To generate ROCK2 knockout mice, a BAC clone containing exon 5 region was isolated and a targeting vector was constructed by inserting a pgk-neomycin\ncassette in the Nco1 site of exon 5 upstream of the predicted kinase domain of\nROCK2\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-2949-9725" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0662-9523" ;
        dc:date           "2017-11-10" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_1788" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

